file=AI & Agents/gauge/operational/commands/gauge-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "agent performance", "quality report", "scorecard", "cost drift", "is X degrading" \| agent-quality-scorecard \| /score \| · tb=\| "monitor models", "golden set", "drift check", "version pin", "provider updated" \| llm-ops-basics \| /golden \| · tb=\| "route this flag", "open cases", "who fixes this", "case status", "stalled" \| degradation-routing \| /route \| · tb=\| "fleet health", "how's the fleet", "weekly report", "dashboard" \| fleet-health-report \| /health \| · p:Precedence=1. Security-smelling language ("weird output", "unexpected egress", "injected") → degradation-routing's security path FIRST, whatever skill was running.\n2. "Is X degrading?" runs scorecard THEN routing — measurement precedes routing, always.\n3. Report requests never trigger new measurement mid-flight; they synthesize the latest artifacts.\n